                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "A dinner party is an event where one person (the host ) invites a group of friends to eat a meal at his or her house. At a traditional dinner party, the host cooks the food: an appetizer and a main course. But the guests usually bring something to drink, and perhaps also a dessert. In a pot luck dinner party, everybody (the host and guests) prepares one or two dishes. It’s called pot luck because it’s always a surprise: nobody knows what the others will bring."
                  ]
